.TH ROSIE 1
.SH NAME
rosie \- quick chat and command generation with Ollama-backed model selection
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rosie
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIPROMPT\fR]...
.PP
.B rosie --ask
[\fI--model MODEL\fR] [\fIPROMPT\fR]...
.PP
.B rosie --cmd
[\fI--model MODEL\fR] [\fIPROMPT\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rosie
supports two explicit non-TUI runtime modes:
.IP \[bu] 2
.B --ask
for one-shot chat responses
.IP \[bu] 2
.B --cmd
for shell command generation with interactive
.B e/r/q
review flow
.PP
When run without
.B --ask
or
.B --cmd,
Rosie launches the full-screen TUI chat interface with sessions, transcript, and composer panes.
In TUI mode, Rosie starts in
.B Normal
mode. Press
.B i
to enter
.B Insert
mode; pressing
.B Enter
sends the composer content to Ollama, and assistant tokens stream into transcript as they arrive.
.B j
/
.B k
(or arrow keys) scroll transcript in
.B Normal
mode.
.B PageUp
/
.B PageDown
perform full-page scrolling, and
.B Ctrl+u
/
.B Ctrl+d
perform half-page scrolling.
.B gg
jumps to top and
.B G
jumps to bottom.
The header displays the active session title/id.
New sessions are auto-titled from the first user message using a concise local heuristic, then refined with a model-generated title when available.
.B Backspace
edits input. Press
.B Esc
to return to
.B Normal
mode. Press
.B :
in
.B Normal
to open the floating command panel (for example:
.B :help ,
.B :session ,
.B :models ,
.B :theme ,
.B :quit
).
In the command panel, use
.B j
/
.B k
(or arrow keys) to select from the command picklist and
.B Enter
to run.
In session manager
.RB ( :session ),
use
.B j
/
.B k
to select,
.B Enter
to switch,
.B n
to create,
.B r
to rename,
and
.B d
to delete (with confirmation).
In the model picker, use
.B j
/
.B k
(or arrow keys) to move, press
.B Enter
to apply to the active session, and
.B Esc
to cancel.
Use
.B :theme
with
.I catppuccin
or
.I rose-pine
to switch TUI themes.
Session model selections persist and are restored when switching sessions or restarting.
Delete actions require confirmation with
.B [Y/n]
(press
.B Enter
for yes).
Press
.B Esc
in
.B Normal
to cancel an in-flight request. Use
.B Ctrl+C
to quit from any mode.
.PP
Prompts can be supplied as trailing arguments or from standard input. If neither is provided in an interactive terminal, Rosie prompts for one line of input.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --configure
Interactively create or update local configuration in
.I ~/.config/rosie/config.toml
(including Ollama host and model defaults).
.TP
.B --install
Install the current binary into the local bin directory and install this man page into the local man directory.
.TP
.BR -a , " --ask"
Run one-shot chat mode and print the answer once.
.TP
.BR -c , " --cmd"
Run command-generation mode (existing non-TUI flow with execute/re-enter/quit prompt).
.TP
.BI --model " MODEL"
Override model selection for this invocation.
.TP
.BR -V , " --version"
Display version information and exit.
.TP
.BR -h , " --help"
Print help information.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Rosie uses file-based configuration for host/model defaults:
.TP
.I ~/.config/rosie/config.toml
(or
.I ${XDG_CONFIG_HOME}/rosie/config.toml
when
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is set).
.PP
Supported keys:
.TP
.B ollama_host
Ollama base URL (default:
.I http://localhost:11434 )
.TP
.B default_model
Global model fallback
.TP
.B ask_model
Mode-specific default for
.B --ask
(optional)
.TP
.B cmd_model
Mode-specific default for
.B --cmd
(optional)
.TP
.B theme
TUI theme name (
.I catppuccin
or
.IR rose-pine )
.TP
.B execution_enabled
If false, command execution is disabled in
.B --cmd
while generation remains available
.PP
Model resolution order:
.IP "1." 4
.B --model
.IP "2." 4
mode-specific default (
.B ask_model
or
.B cmd_model )
.IP "3." 4
.B default_model
.IP "4." 4
first local Ollama model discovered via
.I /api/tags
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/rosie/config.toml
Persistent local configuration written by
.BR rosie " --configure" .
.TP
.I ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/rosie/sessions.sqlite3
Session/message persistence database used by TUI mode.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/rosie/sessions.sqlite3
Default TUI session database path when
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
is unset.
.TP
.I ~/.local/bin/rosie
Default install location for the executable when
.B XDG_BIN_HOME
is unset.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/man/man1/rosie.1
Default install location for this man page when
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
is unset.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Configure Rosie:
.B rosie --configure
.TP
Install Rosie:
.B rosie --install
.TP
Quick chat:
.B rosie --ask "What's the capital of France?"
.TP
Generate a command:
.B rosie --cmd "show top 10 processes by memory"
.TP
Prompt from standard input:
.B echo "find large files" | rosie --cmd
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B rosie
exits with status 0 on success and non-zero on error.
